#31145
The Frjosa Hel-vegr Tundra~
   Looking in any direction proves to be pointless, as it is all white.  
Although, to the north there seems to be a large wall of ice running east to
west.  Visibility is three to five feet at best.  The ground is frozen solid,
the air painfully dry and cold, and the wind feels like daggers.  This is no
place for any sane being.  Unless, you're a polar bear, you best find shelter
and fire soon.  
~
